public class UnconstrainedNode
extends Node
implements ODEEquationPart

A particle not subject to any kinematic constraints. Its motion is fully determined by the forces acting on it.

assumeTimeAndState

public void assumeTimeAndState(double time,
                               ODEState state)
Description copied from interface: ODEEquationPart

Causes the object to assume the time and state given. This method is used for "priming" the object for a subsequent call to getODEStateDerivative during a solution step. It can also be used to update the "real" state of the object after a solution step, in which case the time parameter is insignificant.

Specified by:
assumeTimeAndState in interface ODEEquationPart
Parameters:
time - the assumed time
state - the assumed state
